## Phase 2 — Backend: Cloudinary Resume Upload

> **Goal**: Add secure PDF resume upload via Cloudinary.

### 2A. Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install cloudinary multer multer-storage-cloudinary
```

### 2B. Cloudinary Config

#### [NEW] [cloudinary.js](file:///c:/Users/Alok%20Chandra/cpms-mini-project/backend/config/cloudinary.js)

Configure Cloudinary with env vars: `CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME`, `CLOUDINARY_API_KEY`, `CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET`.

### 2C. Multer Upload Middleware

#### [NEW] [upload.middleware.js](file:///c:/Users/Alok%20Chandra/cpms-mini-project/backend/middleware/upload.middleware.js)

- Accept only PDF files
- Max file size: **2MB**
- Store in Cloudinary folder: `cpms/resumes/{userId}`
- Use `multer-storage-cloudinary` for direct Cloudinary streaming

### 2D. Resume Upload Endpoint

#### [MODIFY] [profile.controller.js](file:///c:/Users/Alok%20Chandra/cpms-mini-project/backend/controllers/profile.controller.js)

| Endpoint | Method | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `/api/profile/resume` | POST | Student | Upload resume (PDF), save URL + publicId. If resume exists, delete old one from Cloudinary first. |
| `/api/profile/resume` | DELETE | Student | Remove resume from Cloudinary & clear fields |

#### [MODIFY] [profile.routes.js](file:///c:/Users/Alok%20Chandra/cpms-mini-project/backend/routes/profile.routes.js)

Add resume upload/delete routes with `upload.single('resume')` middleware.

#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///c:/Users/Alok%20Chandra/cpms-mini-project/backend/.env)

Add Cloudinary credentials:
```
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloud_name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_api_key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_api_secret
```

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///c:/Users/Alok%20Chandra/cpms-mini-project/backend/app.js)

Increase body parser limit for multipart: already handled by multer, but ensure no conflicts with `express.json({ limit })`.

