## Phase 5 — Integration, Profile Completion & Polish

> **Goal**: Wire everything together, handle edge cases, and polish the UX.

### 5A. Profile Completion Logic

#### [MODIFY] [StudentProfile.model.js](file:///c:/Users/Alok%20Chandra/cpms-mini-project/backend/models/StudentProfile.model.js)

Add a method `calculateCompletion()` that scores each field group:

| Section | Weight |
|---|---|
| Personal Info (phone, DOB, gender) | 15% |
| Academic (10th, 12th, CGPA) | 30% |
| Skills (≥3 skills) | 15% |
| Projects (≥1 project) | 15% |
| Resume uploaded | 25% |

On every profile save → recalculate → update `User.profileComplete`.

### 5B. Dashboard Integration

#### [MODIFY] [StudentDashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Alok%20Chandra/cpms-mini-project/frontend/src/pages/dashboard/StudentDashboard.jsx)

- The "Complete Student Profile" step in the Next Steps checklist should link to `/dashboard/student/profile`
- Profile completion ring in the hero banner should reflect real-time profile data

### 5C. Toast Notifications

- Success: "Profile updated successfully ✓"
- Success: "Resume uploaded successfully ✓"
- Error: "Failed to save profile. Please try again."
- Error: "Only PDF files under 2MB are allowed"

### 5D. Loading & Error States

- Skeleton loaders while profile data loads
- Retry button on API errors
- Optimistic UI for quick field edits

